<TEXT>
a deputy police chief resigned under fire 
wednesday as the police commissioner issued a report blaming him 
and other brass for a riot at a park that led to 100 complaints of 
police brutality 
deputy chief thomas darcy a 31year police veteran commanded 
hundreds of police officers who were deployed to defuse a 
demonstration at tompkins square park on manhattans lower east 
side on aug 6 
the demonstration against a 1 am curfew at the park turned 
violent and more than 50 people were hurt in clashes between police 
and protesters more than 100 charges of police brutality were 
later filed with the civilian complaint review board 
commissioner benjamin wards report said a lack of supervision 
was responsible for the appalling behavior of some members of the 
department 
the control of the situation was lost during the first 
confrontation between police and demonstrators and never 
sufficiently regained wrote chief of department robert j 
johnston who prepared the 16page report 
for this chief darcy the highestranking member of the 
department at the scene must be held accountable 
the other two supervisory officers at the confrontation deputy 
inspector joseph wodarski and capt gerald mcnamara also were 
disciplined 
wodarski was the ranking officer at the scene during a crucial 
period when darcy returned to his office about a dozen blocks away 
to go to the bathroom but he deferred all major decisions to 
mcnamara 
unfortunately the report said capt mcnamaras actions 
were not well planned staffed supervised or executed unnecessary 
confrontations resulted which culminated in a riot 
a key mistake according to ward was mcnamaras decision at 
the beginning of the demonstration to transmit an emergency signal 
that mobilized 300 police officers from all over the city without 
making any provisions for adequate supervision of the officers 
even after darcy returned to the park the mobilization call was 
never taken off the air as a result officers continued to pour 
into the area further confusing the situation ward said 
wodarski was reassigned from his prestigious post as commanding 
officer of the midtown south precinct to another as a command in 
queens 
mcnamara will be temporarily removed from his job commanding the 
9th precinct for a six to sevenmonth retraining period ward 
said during that time the east village precinct house will be 
placed under the command of inspector elson gelfand 
the civilian complaint review board has already identified 
several officers involved in the melee relying in part on 
videotapes taken by neighborhood residents the videotapes show 
police officers some of whom covered or removed their badges 
striking demonstrators for no apparent reason 
the board recommended that charges be brought against two 
officers both of whom were placed on modified assignment wednesday 
pending outcome of a departmental trial 
darcy 56 had been criticized anonymously shortly after the 
riot when ward cited the decision by the ranking officer at the 
park to leave the scene to go to the bathroom at a crucial moment 
the commissioner had said that was one of 10 mistakes that led to 
the melee 
darcy was trained in crowd control during the 1960s as a member 
of the tactical patrol force the new york police department was 
widely praised in those years for developing tactics that helped 
the city avoid the widescale civil disorder that plagued many 
other big cities 
