<TEXT>
members of the antiapartheid 
progressive federal party walked out of parliament on thursday to 
protest a government manuever aimed at pushing through 
controversial legislation 
one of the bills would strengthen enforcement of the group areas 
act which mandates racially segregated residential areas another 
would give authorities more powers to evict black squatters 
president pw bothas national party holds an overwhelming 
majority in parliaments white chamber and is able to gain support 
for most legislation from the majority parties in the two smaller 
chambers one for asians and one for people of mixedrace 
the two nonwhite chambers however have refused to consider 
the current bills insisting instead on total repeal of the group 
areas act 
the black majority is excluded from parliament and has no vote 
in national affairs 
the leader of the white chamber fw de klerk announced 
thursday that parliamentary rules would be suspended so the six 
pending bills could be dealt with solely by the white legislators 
progressive federal members said the rule change made a farce of 
the parliamentary process 
you are doing it to pass laws which are repugnant to the vast 
