the city council has voted to let police arrest 
and search people who look or act like drug dealers regardless of 
whether the people are seen making drug deals 
the ordinance approved wednesday also says such loiterers may 
be fined 500 if they are known drug dealers or pass money 
packages or written material to passersby in an area known for 
drug sales 
civil libertarians questioned the ordinance which says someone 
may be arrested who loiters in a public place in a manner and 
under circumstances manifesting the purpose of selling any illegal 
controlled substance 
a known drug dealer is defined as someone who has been convicted 
of drug charges within the last year 
councilman al gonzalez said he proposed the ordinance at the 
request of lou caudell first assistant police chief 
this allows uniformed police officers to get actively involved 
in the war on drugs said police lt doug kowalski 
