requested a courtmartial so he could have an opportunity to clear 
himself 
cmdr newell d krogmann the military judge denied a motion to 
dismiss the second of two counts against torchia the motion 
alleged insufficient evidence 
the judge later thursday heard testimony on a motion to dismiss 
both counts on grounds the chief of naval education and training 
vice adm nr thunman who convened the courtmartial was biased 
against torchia 
krogmann said he would make a decision when proceedings 
reconvene friday the trial will begin if he denies the motion he 
has two other options dismiss the case or remove it from thunman 
and shift it to another admiral of equal or higher responsibility 
for an independent decision on whether a courtmartial is warranted 
thunman ordered the courtmartial against the advice of the 
investigating officer cmdr daniel j dalesio who recommended no 
disciplinary action against torchia 
a guilty verdict could bring torchia up to three months 
confinement loss of pay and a formal reprimand that could make 
future advancement in the navy extremely difficult 
scheduled for trial monday is petty officer 2nd class michael w 
combe 26 of tempe ariz he is charged with involuntary 
manslaughter battery and conspiracy to commit battery 
combe is accused of holding mirecki under the water if 
convicted he could be dishonorably discharged and sentenced to 
prison for more than three years he was denied the option of 
accepting nonjudicial punishment 
