media 
mrs quayle said it had crossed her mind that journalists 
are out to get the republican vicepresidential nominee 
i cant substantiate that she said i think part of it is 
just the fact that there were so many members of the media down in 
new orleans with nothing to do and they decided they would find a 
story and they looked wherever they thought they could and dug 
something up 
she said the race is extraordinarily important to our 
country 
and when you deal in rumors and innuendo instead of dealing 
with the issues that are important to the continuation of the 
success of our country not only is that an insult to every voter 
in this nation but its not fair to the voters she said 
theyve the media gone too far 
mrs quayle said her husband may attract more scrutiny from some 
members of the media because of his conservative views 
i just have the feeling that there is in a great deal of the 
media a bias not only towards republicans but especially towards 
conservative republicans she said and its come out many 
times over its something we deal with all the time 
