<TEXT>
americas economy and corporate profits expanded briskly this 
spring the government said today but the news was overshadowed by 
higher inflation rising interest rates slumping financial markets 
and a slowdown in home sales 
the commerce department said the gross national product the 
broadest measure of economic health rose at an annual rate of 33 
percent from april through june despite severe shock from the 
drought that seared much of the country the gnp rate of expansion 
was unchanged from the first quarter 
without the drought the gnp would have shot up at a 43 percent 
annual rate in the apriljune period 
the government also said aftertax corporate profits shot up 
115 percent in the second quarter following a 25 percent rise in 
the first quarter the performance was the best since a 145 
percent rise in the 1983 second quarter 
but apriljune inflation as measured by a gnp price index rose 
at an annual rate of 51 percent the fastest increase since a 58 
percent rise in the third quarter of 1982 the department said the 
surge was blamed on higher prices for clothes food and fuel 
further obscuring the gnp and corporate profit news was that key 
west european nations raised interest rates today blaming the move 
on the stronger us dollar and consequent weakness in their own 
currencies the increases signaled another round of higher interest 
rates worldwide 
those developments helped incite a selloff in the bond market a 
sensitive barometer of interest rates and the economy the 
treasurys key 30year issue fell nearly 750 per 1000 in face 
amount and its yield rose to 946 percent from 939 percent late 
wednesday 
on wall street where traders were recalling the stock market 
peak a year ago today prices slid as well the dow jones 
industrial average was down about 18 points to the 2008 level by 
late morning 
rising interest rates also played a key role in a 5 percent drop 
in existing singlefamily home sales last month a real estate 
trade group said today the national association of realtors said 
the decline was partly the result of higher mortgage costs 
the developments came a day after the government reported 
americas trade deficit shrank 15 percent in the apriljune 
quarter which heartened republicans fighting to retain the white 
house but didnt impress the financial markets 
the difference between what the united states spends and sells 
abroad narrowed to a deficit of 299 billion in the second 
quarter compared with a 352 billion deficit in the first quarter 
many economists regard the trade deficit as one of the most 
visible weaknesses in the economy reflecting a relentless 
addiction to cheap imports and consequent difficulty for domestic 
companies trying to compete democrats have attempted to make the 
trade deficit an issue in the presidential campaign 
but the improvement reported wednesday suggested us 
manufacturers were making strong gains in selling abroad some 
