of the mark against the us dollar as a main reason for lifting 
the discount rate 
the higher discount rate should cause other interest rates to 
rise that would support the exchange value of the mark by making 
markdenominated investments more attractive 
the dollar eased more than a pfennig to level around 18650 
marks soon after the bundesbanks announcement 
france great britain switzerland the netherlands and austria 
followed the bundesbanks lead and raised rates 
todays step is an important signal which will be understood 
by the foreign exchange and capital markets poehl said 
poehl told reporters that the dollars strength against the mark 
endangered efforts to adjust trade imbalances between the worlds 
major trading partners 
